fisheries improvement director the leopold leadership program skip to main content search this site the leopold leadership program about fellows news fellowship information resources login fellowships positions early career environmental scholars new fellowships new positions fisheries improvement director fisheries improvement director institution sustainable fisheries partnership discipline fisheries management type of position director notes the purpose of the position is to develop maintain and support fishery based relationships in the general vicinity of the gulf of mexico and assist sfp staff as necessary with duties related to global major buyer engagement there are three major areas identified 1 southeast atlantic2 gulf of mexico3 caribbean the overall job is to understand all aspects of fisheries sustainability in your region develop a relationship between sfp and key stakeholders pertaining to each fishery work with the fip members to develop policy briefs and advocacy strategies support fip development throughout your region track monitor and report on fip progress work with the buyer engagement team to define action items for the supply chain in all fips in your region submitted by leopold program staff march 5 2012 deadline open until filled 2012 leopold leadership program the stanford woods institute for the environment stanford university stanford ca 94305
